&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Account Manager &lt;strong&gt;Company:&lt;/strong&gt; Health Link Home Health and Hospice &lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; South Bay Area, CA &lt;strong&gt;Pay:&lt;/strong&gt; $40–$45/hour (based on experience) &lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;For nearly 20 years, Health Link Home Health and Hospice has been a trusted provider of compassionate, high-quality care delivered directly to patients in the comfort of their homes. As we grow our presence across the Bay Area, we are looking for a motivated and personable Account Manager to join our Community Relations team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;As an Account Manager, you will be the face of Health Link in the field — building lasting relationships with referral sources, healthcare providers, and community partners. Your work directly connects patients to the care they need. You will partner closely with the Director of Community Relations to develop your territory, grow our referral network, and position Health Link as the first choice for in-home care across the South Bay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Develop and execute a sales and outreach strategy to grow Health Link&#39;s referral base across your assigned territory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Build and maintain relationships with hospitals, clinics, physician offices, skilled nursing facilities, senior communities, and other healthcare organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Represent Health Link at community events, networking functions, and industry meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Conduct outreach calls, schedule in-person meetings, deliver presentations, and follow up consistently to turn leads into lasting partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Coordinate with the intake team to ensure a smooth referral process and serve as the communication bridge between partners and internal staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Track all outreach activities, contacts, and outcomes using CRM software&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Manage a personal outreach budget responsibly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Participate in ride-alongs and training sessions with senior team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Stay informed on industry trends and competitor activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li cla

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Milpitas, CA&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time | On-Site&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; $165,000–$190,000 annually, commensurate with experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Health Link is a multi-branch home health organization serving the Bay Area. We are seeking an experienced Clinical Manager to lead the clinical operations of our growing South Bay branch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;This role is responsible for the day-to-day clinical performance of the branch, including patient care, staff development, regulatory compliance, quality outcomes, and branch operations. The Clinical Manager works closely with executive leadership to support continued growth while maintaining exceptional clinical standards.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;This is an on-site leadership position based in our Milpitas office.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;The Clinical Manager serves as the senior clinical leader of the South Bay branch and is responsible for the overall performance of clinical operations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;This role oversees clinical staff and collaborates with Intake, Scheduling, QA, and administrative support to ensure efficient operations, high-quality patient care, and achievement of established branch goals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;The Clinical Manager is expected to foster accountability, collaboration, and clinical excellence while supporting a positive and high-performing team culture.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Oversee the daily clinical operations of the South Bay branch&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Ensure high-quality patient care and positive clinical outcomes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Monitor clinician productivity, utilization, and performance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Ensure compliance with federal, state, payer, and accreditation requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Recruit, onboard, mentor, and develop clinical staff&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Conduct performance evaluations and provide ongoing coaching&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Foster a culture of accountability, collaboration, and continuous improvement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Manage clinical escalations, complaints, and service recovery&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&q

&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Licensed Home Health Aide (HHA) — San Francisco Peninsula&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;Health Link Home Health and Hospice is a trusted provider of comprehensive home health services in the greater San Francisco Bay Area. For nearly 20 years, we&#39;ve been dedicated to high-quality care and better outcomes for our patients. As we approach our anniversary, we&#39;re looking for people who share our commitment to join the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;We&#39;re hiring a high-energy, compassionate, organized HHA on the San Francisco Peninsula. You&#39;ll work closely with our Director of Nursing, clinical staff, and front office team to coordinate patient care, and provide daily living and personal care services in patients&#39; homes in line with each established care plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;We offer competitive pay and a flexible schedule that supports work/life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Provide personal care (bathing, dressing, toileting, feeding, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Assist with ambulation, transfers, and range of motion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Meet patient safety needs and use medical equipment safely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Provide skin care to prevent tissue breakdown&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Take vital signs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Proven experience as a home health aide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Ability to monitor vital signs and collect specimens&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Familiarity with basic nutrition and personal hygiene standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Proficiency in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Caring and compassionate personality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay &amp;amp; Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;$28–$33/hr DOE&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;$5,000 sign-on bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response

&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Link Home Health &amp;amp; Hospice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;San Francisco, CA | Full-Time | Monday–Friday | Day Shift&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;$35–$40/hour + Comprehensive Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Are You an LVN Looking for More Than Just a Job?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;At Health Link Hospice, we believe exceptional patient care starts with exceptional employees. For nearly 20 years, we have built a reputation throughout the Bay Area for providing compassionate, high-quality hospice and palliative care while creating a supportive environment where our team members can thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;We are seeking an organized, compassionate, and motivated &lt;strong&gt;Clinical Coordinator (LVN)&lt;/strong&gt; to join our growing Hospice team in San Francisco. If you enjoy collaborating with clinicians, supporting patients and families, solving problems, and making a meaningful impact behind the scenes, we&#39;d love to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Why You&#39;ll Love Working Here&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;✅ Monday–Friday schedule with no weekends&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;✅ Competitive pay and comprehensive benefits package&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;✅ Supportive leadership team that values your contributions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;✅ Opportunities for professional growth and advancement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;✅ Collaborative team culture focused on patient-centered care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;✅ Work that makes a meaningful difference in patients&#39; lives every day&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;As a Clinical Coordinator, you&#39;ll play a critical role in ensuring our patients receive seamless, compassionate care while supporting our clinical team and daily operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Patient Care Coordination&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a key liaison between patients, families, physicians, and hospice clinicians.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate care services and assist with resolving patient care concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support communication across the interdisciplinary team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Clinical Documentation &amp;amp; Orders&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Request, track, clarify, and process physician orders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Upload and manage documentation within the EMR system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure records are complete, accurate, and compliant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with clinical documentation and workflow management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Clinical Operations&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support field clinicians with scheduling and care coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and maintain medical supply inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the supply room remains organized and OSHA compliant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with audits, quality improvement initiatives, and regulatory readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Team Support&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with onboarding and orienting new team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with nurses, social workers, chaplains, physicians, and leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a positive and supportive team culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Required&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current California LVN License in good standing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and customer service skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational and multitasking abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and pr

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hospice QA Lead (RN) – Clinical Compliance &amp;amp; Chart Review&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;San Francisco&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time | On-Site&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; $55 – $65/hour DOE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In hospice, the care we provide matters deeply—and the way we document that care ensures patients receive the support they need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Hospice QA Lead based in our San Francisco office, focused on chart review, documentation accuracy, and regulatory compliance. In this role, you will help ensure that each patient’s clinical needs, eligibility, and care are clearly and accurately reflected in the chart, while keeping the agency aligned with ACHC standards and Medicare requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a detail-oriented, supportive role for someone who values both quality care and the documentation that stands behind it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Perform daily chart audits for hospice patients&lt;br&gt;• Ensure compliance with Medicare hospice regulations and ACHC standards&lt;br&gt;• Review and validate certifications and recertifications, face-to-face encounters, hospice eligibility, and documentation of decline&lt;br&gt;• Review plans of care and visit documentation for accuracy and completeness&lt;br&gt;• Identify documentation gaps and support timely corrections&lt;br&gt;• Track trends in live discharges, revocations, length of stay, and documentation inconsistencies&lt;br&gt;• Partner with clinical leadership to ensure follow-through and accountability&lt;br&gt;• Maintain ongoing survey readiness through consistent chart review&lt;br&gt;• Provide clear, constructive feedback to clinicians to strengthen documentation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Active RN license (California)&lt;br&gt;• Hospice experience required&lt;br&gt;• Strong understanding of hospice eligibility, recertification requirements, and documentation supporting terminal prognosis and decline&lt;br&gt;• Knowledge of Medicare hospice compliance standards&lt;br&gt;• Experience in QA, auditing, or clinical review preferred&lt;br&gt;• Strong attention to detail with a patient-centered mindset&lt;br&gt;• Ability to communicate clearly and work collaboratively with clinicians&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why This Role Matters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ensures patients are appropriately supported with hospice services&lt;br&gt;• Strengthens the accuracy and completeness of clinical documentation&lt;br&gt;• Maintains compliance and ongoing survey readiness&lt;br&gt;• Supports clinicians in delivering high-quality, well-documented care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who This Role Is For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• You are detail-oriented but also see the bigger picture&lt;br&gt;• You take pride in doing things the right way&lt;br&gt;• You enjoy supporting clinicians and strengthening processes&lt;br&gt;• You believe that good documentation helps tell the full story of patient care&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot;&gt;Hospice Registered Nurse (RN)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt; Health Link Home Health and Hospice is a renowned provider of comprehensive home health services in the greater San Francisco Bay Area. For nearly 20 years, we have been dedicated to delivering high-quality care and improving healthcare outcomes for our patients. As we approach our milestone anniversary, we are seeking compassionate individuals who share our commitment to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id=&quot;p-rc_8ba547c8def06ba1-33&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt; We are currently looking for a compassionate, organized, and team-oriented Hospice Registe&lt;span class=&quot;citation-276 citation-277 citation-end-277&quot;&gt;red Nurse (RN) to support our patients in the San Francisco Bay Area.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id=&quot;p-rc_8ba547c8def06ba1-34&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-274 citation-275 citation-end-275&quot;&gt;In this essential role, you will evaluate the overall health of terminally ill patients and provide dedicated nursing care aimed at improving their quality of life. You will work closely with our Director of Nursing, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-274 citation-end-274&quot;&gt;clinical staff, a&lt;/span&gt;nd front office team to ensure coordinated, high-quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;6&quot;&gt;At Health Link Hospice, we foster a collaborative and supportive work environment. One of the unique aspects of our agency is the seamless support provided by our back-office team. By handling the administrative heavy lifting, our office team enables you to work remotely and independently in the field, maximizing your efficiency so you can focus entirely on patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;7&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;7&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Job Types Available:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; Per Diem&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;8&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;8&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;9&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;9,0,0&quot;&gt;Provide services within the scope of nursing, adhering strictly to each patient&#39;s individualized plan of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;9,1,0&quot;&gt;Coordinate seamlessly with our interdisciplinary care team to ensure holistic patient support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;9,2,0&quot;&gt;Administer treatments and carefully evaluate patient reactions and progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;9,3,0&quot;&gt;Promptly report any changes in a patient&#39;s condition to the Hospice Clinical Director.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;9,4,0&quot;&gt;Complete all clinical charting (using Kinnser) in a timely manner on company-provided devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;9,5,0&quot;&gt;Ensure compliance with all company policies, procedures, and safety guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-path-to-node=&quot;10&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Requirements and Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;11

&lt;h3 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold&quot;&gt;Human Resources Coordinator&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Link Home Health and Hospice&lt;/strong&gt; | San Francisco, CA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On-site&lt;/strong&gt; · Full-time · $30–$35/hour DOE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold&quot;&gt;Who we are&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;For more than two decades, Health Link has delivered compassionate home health and hospice care to families across the Bay Area. Our work is personal — we show up for patients during some of the most meaningful chapters of their lives. The people who do that work deserve to feel just as supported as the patients they serve, and that&#39;s exactly what this role is about.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold&quot;&gt;Why this role exists&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;We&#39;re looking for an HR Coordinator who will genuinely take ownership of the employee experience at Health Link — someone our staff can turn to and trust, and someone who treats the regulatory rigor of home health as part of how we care for our people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Our clinicians and administrative teams pour themselves into caring for patients; they need an HR partner who pours that same energy back into them and who keeps the credentials, documentation, and compliance standards that protect them airtight in the process. In home health, sloppy paperwork isn&#39;t a clerical issue; it&#39;s a patient safety issue and a staff protection issue. We need someone who understands that and brings real care to both sides of the work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;This isn&#39;t a role where you wait to be told what&#39;s needed. You&#39;ll see the gaps, ask the questions, and build the systems and relationships that make people feel supported &lt;em&gt;and&lt;/em&gt; keep us audit-ready. If the idea of being the person staff can count on for the small things, the hard things, and the regulated things energizes you, keep reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold&quot;&gt;What you&#39;ll own&lt;/h4&gt;
