&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Home Health Occupational Therapist (OT)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Per Diem | San Francisco or San Mateo County — Dedicated Territory Assigned&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are currently looking for a compassionate, organized, and team-oriented individual to fill the role of Occupational Therapist (OT) position for the SF &amp;amp;&amp;nbsp; Peninsula area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Where great OTs come to do their best work.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Health Link Home Health &amp;amp; Hospice, we believe great patient care starts with supporting the clinicians who deliver it. For over 20 years, we&#39;ve served the greater Bay Area with a focus on clinical quality, strong systems, and a collaborative culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring Occupational Therapists for Peninsula teams. You will be assigned to one dedicated territory —&amp;nbsp; San Mateo County — so you can build familiarity with your patients and your area without being stretched across both.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why OTs Choose Health Link&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dedicated Territory:&lt;/strong&gt; Your caseload stays within a manageable radius in either SF or the Peninsula — no crossing bridges or unpredictable commutes. SF patients are spread across neighborhoods like the Sunset, Richmond, and Mission; Peninsula patients run from Daly City down through Redwood City.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SF Rideshare Support:&lt;/strong&gt; If you take the SF territory, company-provided rideshare credits (Uber/Lyft) help cover travel to and from patient visits so you can focus on care, not logistics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI-Assisted Documentation:&lt;/strong&gt; We use AI-assisted charting so you spend less time on notes and more time with patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Support:&lt;/strong&gt; You are never alone. Our experienced case managers and clinical team are available in real-time to assist with complex situations or patient coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation &amp;amp; Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; $125,000 – $150,000 per year (based on experience)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance Bonus:&lt;/strong&gt; Up to 25% of base salary tied to quality metrics and clinical outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Earning Potential:&lt;/strong&gt; $156,250 – $187,500 per year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health:&lt;/strong&gt; Medical, dental, vision, life, and pet insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Retirement:&lt;/strong&gt; 401(k) with employer matching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perks:&lt;/strong&gt; Paid time off, vehicle reimbursement options, and company-provided devices (iPad)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide skilled occupational therapy services focused on ADLs, adaptive equipment, and functional independence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, implement, and manage individualized plans of care based on physician orders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report changes in patient condition and collaborate with physicians, case managers, and the Director of Nursing&lt;/li&gt;
